FIRST NAT. BANK OF BROWNSVILLE, TEX., v. FLEITMANN et al. (No. 7363.) (Supreme Court, Appellate Division, First Department. June 4, 1915.) Appeal from Special Term, First Department. Action by the First National Bank of Brownsville, Tex., against Lida M. Fleitmann and another. Demurrer to answer sustained, motion to resettle order denied, and plaintiff appeals. Affirmed.

Argued before INGRAHAM, P. J., and McLAUGHLIN, LAUGHLIN, DOWLING, and HOTCHKISS, JJ.

PER CURIAM.

Order affirmed, with $10 costs and disbursements.
